item.description:
A repository to keep track of random little things I learned each day.
Observation matrix (2023/11/13) Observation matrix, \(M\), is defined as
\begin{equation} m_{\rm out} = M m_{\rm in}. \end{equation}
The sky signal observed by detectors, \(s\), is given by
\begin{equation} s = Pm_{\rm in}, \end{equation}
where \(P\) is the pointing matrix. It can be solved by
\begin{equation} m = (P^{T}N^{-1}P)^{-1}P^TN^{-1}s \equiv Bs, \end{equation}
where \(N\) is the noise covariance matrix.
